    <section class="container">
        <h2 class="intro-heading">Hands-On Craft Camp curates immersive creative experiences for children</h2>
        <p class="intro-text">In an increasingly digital world, working with one's hands fosters creativity, patience, and problem-solving in ways that screens cannot. Our camp is designed to nurture this connection between mind and body, giving kids a chance to develop skills that have been removed from most school curriculums.</p>
        
        <div class="approaches" id="approaches">
            <div class="approach">
                <h2>Deep Dive Approach</h2>
                <p>Focusing on one craft per session, this format allows campers to develop a higher level of skill and confidence. Each break session is dedicated to a single craft, culminating in an advanced final project.</p>
                
                <h3>School Year Calendar</h3>
                <ul class="calendar" id="calendar">
                    <li><strong>Fall Break</strong> Printmaking – Design, carve, and print a series of block prints, culminating in a framed piece or a set of printed textiles.</li>
                    <li><strong>Winter Break</strong> Sewing – Learn pattern-making, stitching, and embellishments, creating a wearable garment or functional textile item.</li>
                    <li><strong>Spring Break</strong> Leatherwork – Cutting, stitching, and tooling leather to create a finished bag, belt, or wallet.</li>
                    <li><strong>Summer Break</strong> Stone Setting – Setting stones into pendants, rings, or decorative objects using bezel and prong settings.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="approach">
                <h2>Craft Sampler Approach</h2>
                <p>This approach introduces students to multiple crafts, providing a hands-on experience with a variety of materials and techniques.</p>
                
                <h3>School Year Calendar</h3>
                <ul class="calendar">
                    <li><strong>Fall Break</strong> Introduction to Printmaking & Sewing (Mini projects in both crafts)</li>
                    <li><strong>Winter Break</strong> Leatherwork & Stone Setting (Basic projects in each skill)</li>
                    <li><strong>Spring Break</strong> Spoon Carving & Printmaking (Creating functional wooden objects and printing custom designs)</li>
                    <li><strong>Summer Break</strong> Mixed Materials Challenge – Combining techniques from all disciplines to create a multi-material final project.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="approach">
                <h2>Integrated & Experimental</h2>
                <p>This version blends traditional craft techniques with other creative disciplines like storytelling, sculpture, and practical applications.</p>
                
                <h3>School Year Calendar</h3>
                <ul class="calendar">
                    <li><strong>Fall Break</strong> Craft & Storytelling – Create hand-bound illustrated books using printmaking and sewing.</li>
                    <li><strong>Winter Break</strong> Wearable Art – Combine sewing, leatherwork, and stone setting to design and create personal adornments.</li>
                    <li><strong>Spring Break</strong> Function & Form – Focus on practical, usable items like carved wooden spoons, stitched pouches, and printed fabrics for daily use.</li>
                    <li><strong>Summer Break</strong> Freestyle Maker's Lab – A guided, open-ended workshop where kids combine multiple crafts to create their own final projects.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="cta" id="enroll">
        <h2>Give Your Child the Gift of Craft</h2>
        <p>Each session ensures kids leave with a completed project and an understanding of the materials, history, and techniques behind their work. Through this program, we hope to instill confidence, patience, and an appreciation for the hands-on arts that bring imagination to life.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn">Enroll Now</a>
    </section>
    
